<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900413-0051</DOCNO><DOCID>900413-0051.</DOCID><HL>   Corrections andamp; Amplifications:   Browning-Ferris Industries Inc.</HL><DATE>04/13/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6</SO><LP>   CORNING Inc. has not filed a patent infringement suitagainst SpecTran Corp., a maker of optical fibers. An earlieredition incorrectly reported that Corning had filed such asuit to protect infringements against its optical fiberpatents.   (See: &quot;Corning Boosts Fiber Output Capacity And DesignsTougher Fiber-Optic Cable&quot; -- WSJ March 20, 1990)</LP><TEXT>   ---   BROWNING-FERRIS INDUSTRIES Inc. is pulling out of thehazardous waste treatment and disposal business and isclosing or attempting to sell its hazardous-waste landfills.An earlier edition reported that the company was leaving thelandfill business entirely. Browning-Ferris continues tooperate solid-waste landfills.   (See: &quot;Inside Track: Environmental Firm Executives CutHoldings in Their Companies&quot; -- WSJ April 11, 1990)</TEXT></DOC>